<i>He now shares the lead</i>
<i>in the World Championship with 18 points.</i>

01:50:29.589 --> 01:50:33.582
<i>Exactly the same as the Ferrari driver,</i>
<i>Jean-Pierre Sarti, the Frenchman.</i>

01:50:33.760 --> 01:50:37.924
<i>Sarti's best practice time so far</i>
<i>on this 2.6 Mile Zandvoort circuit...</i>

01:50:38.098 --> 01:50:40.362
<i>is one minute, 27.1.</i>

01:50:40.533 --> 01:50:44.162
<i>Now, here's Stoddard's best lap.</i>
<i>One minute, 25.9.</i>

01:50:44.337 --> 01:50:46.498
<i>The fastest lap ever on this circuit.</i>

01:50:46.673 --> 01:50:49.699
<i>What a wonderful comeback</i>
<i>for this brave young driver.</i>

01:54:20.386 --> 01:54:23.878
What a shame.
He's falling off.

01:54:45.278 --> 01:54:46.267
Cheers.

01:54:46.446 --> 01:54:48.311
Cheers.

01:55:10.136 --> 01:55:11.501
Then it seems to be all right?

01:55:11.671 --> 01:55:15.198
Of course it seems to be all right.
It's always all right when you're around.

01:55:15.375 --> 01:55:17.172
Then there is nothing wrong, is there?

01:55:17.343 --> 01:55:20.437
It stuck in practice yesterday,
and it still doesn't feel right.

01:55:20.613 --> 01:55:23.878
- But it doesn't stick now!
- I'm telling you, it does!

01:55:24.050 --> 01:55:27.213
Jean-Pierre, just because
you have been running badly lately...

01:55:27.387 --> 01:55:29.514
it's no reason
to take these things out on me.

01:55:29.689 --> 01:55:31.884
If you want a day off this afternoon,
just say so.

01:55:32.058 --> 01:55:35.459
I'm here to race. Understand?

01:55:35.628 --> 01:55:38.426
- To race.
- Okay, be quiet.

01:55:43.469 --> 01:55:46.563
There you are, my beauty.

01:55:51.878 --> 01:55:56.815
- See if it's all there, will you, my man?
- It better all be there. Half of it's mine.

01:56:01.354 --> 01:56:06.314
Does that look like $17,000 to you?

01:56:07.827 --> 01:56:09.192
Yeah.

01:56:11.931 --> 01:56:13.421
Marvel.

01:56:13.600 --> 01:56:18.435
That's what you are, Scott.
A bloody marvel.

01:56:39.926 --> 01:56:44.488
Here. You know,
of course, what you did here.

01:56:44.697 --> 01:56:47.325
I know. I don't have to
see it up there to know.

01:56:48.101 --> 01:56:51.696
It's bad enough to lose
without having to watch yourself do it.

01:56:51.871 --> 01:56:53.896
What's the point of this anyway?

01:56:54.073 --> 01:56:59.306
To see if we can determine
why you are losing.

01:56:59.812 --> 01:57:02.303
Well, you're not gonna find
the answer up there.

01:57:02.482 --> 01:57:06.612
What about your other two drivers?
Why aren't they here? Why only me?

01:57:06.786 --> 01:57:12.452
Because they are not winners.
But you are.

01:57:12.992 --> 01:57:16.120
You are losing to a man who needs...

01:57:16.295 --> 01:57:20.629
almost to be carried
to and from his car.

01:57:20.800 --> 01:57:23.268
How can that be?

01:57:26.072 --> 01:57:29.098
Because he's driving better than I am.
He's making fewer mistakes.

01:57:29.275 --> 01:57:32.403
- That's why anyone wins.
- Exactly.

01:57:32.578 --> 01:57:38.141
Now, shall we turn our attention
to the mistakes?

01:57:52.165 --> 01:57:54.224
About-face.

01:57:56.736 --> 01:58:00.263
By the left, quick march.

